## Audience 4: Archival Package for Future Auditors and Successors

The authorization package archived today is designed not just for compliance storage but for future usability. A future ISSO who joins MyClinic in two years should be able to open the authorization package and understand: what the system is, why it was categorized as High, what controls were implemented, what the assessment found, what was remediated, what is still open, and why the AO made the decision they did.

Documents that are technically present but practically unusable because they lack context produce the institutional continuity problem described in Day 67's reflection — security knowledge that lives only in the current ISSO's head.

The archival package includes a **README document** — a one-page orientation guide for future reviewers that summarizes: the system description in plain language; the authorization timeline (key decisions and dates); the most important risks and how they were handled; where to find each document in the package; and what the current POA&M status is as of the archival date.

The README is not a required NIST artifact. It is a practical investment in the organization's security program continuity — the difference between a future ISSO who can get up to speed in an hour and one who needs weeks to reconstruct the context from documents that don't cross-reference each other.

**Authorization Package Archival Structure:**
```
MCOPENMRS-001 Authorization Package — [date]
│
├── README — Orientation Guide for Future Reviewers
├── 01 — Authorization Decision Document (signed)
├── 02 — Executive Summary
├── 03 — System Security Plan v1.1.3
│   └── Appendices A through H
├── 04 — Security Assessment Report (post-remediation)
│   └── Assessment Evidence Package
├── 05 — Plan of Action and Milestones v2.0
├── 06 — Risk Determination Statement
├── Risk Response Record
├── 07 — Formal Categorization Record
├── 08 — Tailoring Decision Record
├── 09 — Continuous Monitoring Strategy v2
└── 10 — Authorization Notification Communications
    ├── Governance Stakeholder Memo
    └── All-Staff Communication
```

